{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in the figures, the minGPT model (blue lines in figures) reproduces the distribution accurately for all three properties.",
    "In contrast, the other two diffusionbased models (green & red lines) tend to produce narrower distributions for various properties compared to the training data.",
    "The quantitative evaluation is based on the difference calculation of two distributions using Kullback-Leibler (KL) divergence.",
    "Finally, in terms of computational costs, the minGPT model is more efficient in both training and inference compared to the diffusion-based models.",
    "Training the optimal minGPT model requires around 3-4 mins on a Tesla V100 GPU core (16GB RAM), while both optimal 1Ddiffusion and diffusion-LM models take about 2 hours to train."
  ]
}